Celero
------------------------------------------
Developing consistent and meaningful benchmark results for code is a complex
task. Measurement tools exist (Intel VTune Amplifier, SmartBear AQTime,
Valgrind) external to applications, but they are sometimes expensive for small
teams or cumbersome to utilize. This project, Celero, aims to be a small
library which can be added to a C++ project and perform benchmarks on code in a
way which is easy to reproduce, share, and compare among individual runs,
developers, or projects. Celero uses a framework similar to that of GoogleTest
to make its API easier to use and integrate into a project. Make automated
benchmarking as much a part of your development process as automated testing.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.4.6-1
  libcelero-devel-2.8.5-1bl1
  libcelero2-2.8.5-1bl1
  libgcc1-11.3.0-1
  libstdc++6-11.3.0-1
  pkg-config-1.9.4-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.40-1
  cmake-3.23.2-1
  cygport-0.36.1-1
  gcc-core-11.3.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.3.0-1
  ninja-1.11.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/DigitalInBlue/Celero

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/DigitalInBlue/Celero/archive/refs/tags/v2.8.5.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack Celero-2.8.5-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./Celero-2.8.5-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/Celero-2.8.5-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/Celero-2.8.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcelero2-2.8.5-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libcelero-devel-2.8.5-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

